<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: First-letter with the 'hebrew punctuation maqaf' punctuation character</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/selector.html#first-letter" />
        <meta name="flags" content="" />
        <meta name="assert" content="The 'hebrew punctuation maqaf' is now a Unicode punctuation class (Pd) ('Punctuation Dash') in Unicode 5.1 and is no longer considered part of a class for first-letter to select multiple characters." />
        <style type="text/css">
            div:first-letter
            {
                color: green;
                font-size: 36px;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if only the first character is green.</p>
        <div>&#x05BE;T&#x05BE;</div>
    </body>
</html>